//                    Constructor
// constructor is a member function of a class
// the name of a constructor is the same as the name of the calss
// construtor has no return type
// a constructor is a special method that is used to initialize a newly created object and is called implicity ,just after the memory is allocated for the object
// its not mandatory for coder to write a constructor for class
// when there is no constructor defined in the class by programmer ,compiler implicity provide a default constructor for class
